,Not Recommended,243280,8599500,"Posted: 6 January, 2014",all,Gentle Dementia,"This is a game concept seen in countless flash games.  Simple gamplay centered around an upgrade system and meta-missions (i.e. 'survive for 1:30', 'get a combo of x10', etc).  The only differences are, It's probably the worst execution of the concept I've ever played, and I had to pay eight dollars to play it.  There's no free agency, you can only get the upgrades in a set order, you don't gather any sort of currency, you're just given three missions and when you complete the set you get an upgrade.  The gameplay itself is awful.  Shallow and clunky.  There's no real difficulty, just frustration from hits that shouldn't have happened and crap like that.  Don't get it.  Just go play one of the many, many better ones on Kongregate or something."
