76561198073841664,Recommended,243280,13652648,"Posted: 27 December, 2014",all,gonzo191,"Poof is a mix of action, platformer, tower defence where you play as a dog protecting a cat from enemies which spawn from doors and move around the stage until they reach the cat. Developed by the creators of Hell Yeah! Poof is a simpler game in comparison and I like it for that as Hell Yeah! tried to do too many things and had a complicated control scheme which was nearly impossible to play comfortably.Pros:- Fun action platformer tower defence mash up- Challenge scales as you unlock more items\tower types- Has a somewhat strategic flavour in late gameCons:- No options menu (If you're into that sort of thing)- Extremely repetitive as it has only 1 map- Controls sometimes feel imprecise- Sound effects glitch and mute themselves (Resolved by quitting to the main menu)Verdict:Poof is a fun action platformer tower defence mash up which gets both repetitive and challenging later on but doesn't overstay it welcome and is definitely worth the money."
